TITLE: Using toClass Method for Mongoose Model Instances in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates the use of the toClass method added by Ts.ED to convert Mongoose model instances to the expected class type. It shows how to retrieve a Product instance from a Mongoose query result.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tsedio/tsed/blob/production/docs/tutorials/mongoose.md#2025-04-16_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import {Inject, Injectable} from "@tsed/di";
import {MongooseModel} from "@tsed/mongoose";
import {Product} from "./models/Product";

@Injectable()
export class MyRepository {
  @Inject(Product)
  private model: MongooseModel<Product>;

